In the Description field paste this — ARIA reads this to know when to call the tool:
Creates a database access request ticket in Freshservice.
Call this tool ONLY when ALL of these are true:
1. You have collected all 4 fields: domain, database, role, user_email
2. You have summarised the request back to the user
3. The user has explicitly confirmed with yes, ok, or proceed
Do NOT call before confirmation under any circumstances.




Find the Input schema or Parameters section in the tool editor
Switch to JSON view if available and paste this:

{
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["domain", "database", "role", "user_email"],
  "properties": {
    "domain": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The AD domain. Examples: CORP, APAC, EU. Confirmed by user."
    },
    "database": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Database name. Examples: ProductionDB, SalesDB. Confirmed by user."
    },
    "role": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": [
        "Viewer",
        "Admin",
        "Developer"
      ],
      "description": "Access role. Must be exactly one of the enum values."
    },
    "user_email": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Email of person who needs access. Confirmed by user."
    }
  }
}


Find the Body section in the tool editor → make sure it is set to JSON mode
Paste this exactly — these are the only fields your Cloud Function needs:
{{
  {
    "user_id": current_user.email,
    "metadata": {
      "domain": tool_input.domain,
      "database": tool_input.database,
      "role": tool_input.role,
      "user_email": tool_input.user_email
    }
  }
}}
What each line does
user_id
Retool logged-in user email — becomes the Freshservice requester
metadata.domain
→ custom_fields.domain in Freshservice
metadata.database
→ custom_fields.database in Freshservice
metadata.role
→ custom_fields.role in Freshservice
metadata.user_email
→ custom_fields.user_email in Freshservice
